      • editMap

        public GameMap editMap(java.lang.String mapName)
        Loads map as GameMap object for editing. If the map file does not exist, creates a new GameMap object to add information.
        Parameters:
        mapName - Name of the map to be searched/created
        Returns:
        map object representing the existing map or null value if new one is to be created

      • loadMap

        public GameMap loadMap(java.lang.String mapName)
        Loads map as GameMap object for playing the game. If map file does not exist, it reflects the command as invalid command.
        Parameters:
        mapName - name of the map to be used for playing the game
        Returns:
        map representing the existing map to be used for game play

      • addContinent

        public boolean addContinent(GameMap map,
                            java.lang.String continentName,
                            int controlValue)
        Add continent with given name and control value if it is valid entry. Invalid if continent already exists.
        Parameters:
        map - GameMap representing the map to which continent is to be added
        continentName - Name of the continent to be added
        controlValue - Control value of the continent to be added
        Returns:
        true if valid entry, else false indicating invalid command

      • removeContinent

        public boolean removeContinent(GameMap map,
                               java.lang.String continentName)
        Removes the continent and all the countries present in that continent. Removes neighboring node for all the countries being removed.
        Parameters:
        map - GameMap object representing the map being edited
        continentName - Name of the continent to be removed
        Returns:
        true if successful, else false indicating invalid command

      • addCountry

        public boolean addCountry(GameMap map,
                          java.lang.String countryName,
                          java.lang.String continentName)
        Add country to the map as per the argument parameters if it is a valid entry. Invalid if country already exists.
        Parameters:
        map - GameMap representing the map to which country is to be added
        countryName - Name of the country which is to be added
        continentName - Name of the continent to which this new country belongs
        Returns:
        true if valid entry, else false indicating invalid command

        Parameters:

      • validateMap

        public boolean validateMap(GameMap map)
        Runs various validity checks to ensure that map is suitable for playing the game. Checks: 1) If any empty continent is present, i.e. continent without any country 2) If each continent is a connected sub-graph 3) If map for the game is connected graph or not
        Parameters:
        map - GameMap representing the map
        Returns:
        returns true if valid map, else false indicating invalid map
